Olivia, once again, is in need of replacing her tractor's tire which she will do in her workshop.
To get the tire into her workshop she needs to roll her replacement tire which has a mass of 
[`[$m]\ \textrm{kg}`] and a radius [`r = [$r_cm]\ \textrm{cm}`] over a 
step of height [`h = [$h_cm]\ \textrm{cm}`] off the ground.
Olivia needs to roll the tire such that once it contacts point [`\textrm{P}`] it strikes the step into the workshop and rolls over it without slipping or rebounding. The tire needs to rotate about point [`\textrm{P}`] with an angular velocity [`\omega = [$w2]\ \textrm{rad/s}`] if it is to have enough energy to make it into the workshop on the first try. 

Given that the tire has a radius of gyration [`k = [$k_cm]\ \textrm{cm}`], find the magnitude of minimum initial angular velocity required
to roll the tire over the step on the first try.

[`\omega = `] [__________]{"$w1"} [`\textrm{rad/s}`]

END_PGML

